    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Ingest webhook payloads with MySQL on autopilot\n\n**Pattern:** Webhook Pipeline · **Level:** Architect · **Trigger:** Webhook\n\n## What it does\nIngest webhook payloads with MySQL on autopilot. It fires the moment an external system calls its webhook.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual migration is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nReceive Inbound Webhook → Read Pending Queue (MySQL) → Keep Valid Records → Work in Batches → Aggregate Batch Results → Mark Completed in Notion → Load Previous Snapshot → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to webhook pipeline without manual effort\n- Anyone automating migration in data\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Saves hours of manual work each week\n- Keeps your systems in sync\n- Standardizes the process every time\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: API key / bearer for the target API; Google OAuth2 / service account; MySQL connection; Notion integration token; Slack OAuth2.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.",
        "width": 480,
        "height": 900
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -830,
        80
      ],
      "id": "b352474f-305c-e69e-0327-1da8653abd49",
      "name": "📘 Workflow Overview"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Failures are also parked in a dead-letter queue for replay. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 3
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -230,
        -20
      ],
      "id": "07daaea6-ffed-502b-12d8-01834faebc42",
      "name": "🛟 Error handling & retries"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## ⏱ Rate limiting\n\nWork is batched and spaced with Wait so provider quotas aren't tripped. If you hit 429s, lower the batch size or raise the wait — throughput drops, reliability rises.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 1
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        190,
        -20
      ],
      "id": "0feb86e7-a9dd-085b-bc2f-a17cc44a95e6",
      "name": "⏱ Rate limiting"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🔐 Security\n\nNever trust inbound payloads: the webhook path is unguessable. Add header auth or IP allow-listing for defense in depth. Secrets live in n8n credentials — never in node parameters.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 1
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        610,
        -20
      ],
      "id": "c147173f-b659-321e-6273-97de67d3ec54",
      "name": "🔐 Security"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your migration process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.",
